page.title: 19Life in Wall Heath [2]
page.content: Wallheath is very near Kingswinford which is in the South of the West Midlands.It is also on the edge of the greenbelt and on the border of Staffordshire.My house is on the main road through Wallheath(A449).I go to Summerhill High School.There are also two primary schools,Maidensbridge CP and Ascension Church School.I am the first generation of my family to grow up in Wallheath.My dad comes from Netherton,which is a few miles from Wallheath,and my mom from Sheffield. Dad met her while at Sheffield University.The shops in Wallheath are scattered but are mainly near the cross or on the main road.My mom does most of her shopping at the shopping precinct. Shops seem to have a job staying open. The Co-op has closed and the other supermarket is always closing down and reopening.
